title: Local colleges: Clarkson’s Arasu named LL top volleyball performer
text:
A A 
Clarkson University senior Aishvina Arasu picked up Liberty League volleyball performer of the week for a third time this season after her showing this weekend. 
Arasu averaged 4.89 kills per set and battered opponents to the tune of a .398 hitting percentage over the course of nine sets in three wins at the Clarkson Invitational. 
The Golden Knights swept the women’s cross country honors as junior Victoria Hathaway and freshman Sarah Duclos were named performer and rookie of the week, respectively. 
St. Lawrence University freshman John Lauria’s second-place finish helped the Saints to the team title in the 8-team Nazareth Invitational and he won men’s golf rookie of the week honors. 
St. Lawrence’s Alec Dietsch, Mitchell Gallagher (football), Kara Pelosi (field hockey) and Clarkson’s Scott Henning (men’s golf) were selected to the league honor roll.
